# Custom Spotify Playback Widget

This is a widget created in Python to display your current Spotify playback in a little window in the corner of your screen.

## Installation requirements

This script runs on any version of Python supported by the Pillow library. As of writing, the latest version (Pillow 10.1) supports Python 3.8 through 3.12.


In addition to tkinter, you'll also need the following libraries installed.

1. `Pillow`
## Setup

After cloning the repository, you'll need to create a `.env` file, preferrably in the root of the directory.

Your .env file should contain the following:

```env
SPOTIPY_CLIENT_ID=<your spotify client ID here>
SPOTIPY_CLIENT_SECRET=<your spotify client secret here>
SPOTIPY_REDIRECT_URI=<whatever URI is set up in your spotify application.>```